name: The Wet Spot teadress
description:
Specially designed and made as the uniform for the fantastic Leeds based show hosted and run by Ryvita Von Cheese.
Button up front, with two skirt patch pockets and contrast collar.
Puff sleeves with button cuffs, gathered bust and tie waist for multiple sized dresses.
This can be made in any two colour combination EXCEPT RED/BLACK as this is the specialty colour for "The Wet Spot"  Each  and every dress is made to order in the uk so can be customised to your colour, size or print specification. Please state if you need a bigger size and  two colours/prints specification when ordering.

name: Vintage lace garter
description:
Handmade garter made with vintage lace.
Can be made in any colour or style or with any embelishments.
Lovely for brides -to-be, burlesque, hen parties etc.
It comes in a vintage style presentation tin.

name: Gaza Strip; burlesque & cabaret
description:
Saturday november 9th 2013
£8 in advance
£10 otd
Tickets will be posted up to a week before the event, if purchased after the 7th november, tickets will be collected on the door.

This vaudeville, burlesque & cabaret show will be an extravaganza of tease & sleaze, Decadence & frivolity, 
featuring only the very best national & international acts.

Special guest host..Cherryfox

Steve Las Pistolas
The Great Aziz
Magenta Lust
Kim Khaos
Aurora Winterborn
Julie Jones


And our amazing and beautiful stage manager miss trixie passion! 

The show will be held at The Nines, a beautiful cabaret club with stage level seating and balcony, (5-15 Dalkeith street, Barrow-in-Furness, LA14 1SP) with a fully seated venue decked out to create an unforgettable atmosphere and a unique event experience! 

Dress Code;

Even though there is no official dress code we really appriciate it if our audience gets into the spirit and glam's up for the frivolities - corsets, suits, spatz, boas, hats, tux, evening dress are all accepted.
Dapper chaps and Delightful chapettes.
pin-up queens and bequiffed gents.
Suits and dresses.
Vintage gals and retro guys.
Although if this isn't your bag don't worry yourself silly :D 

Doors open 8pm, first acts are on at 9pm, we will have two intervals for smoking, toileting, etc... 

We are hoping for a sell out show, therefore available on a first come first served basis.
Tickets are non-returnable/non-refundable.
Over 18’s only - bring some ID if you think you might need it ;p
